18/05/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Authorities warned on Monday (May 17th) of potential flooding in the north, west and central regions of Romania due to torrential rains that may cause rivers to swamp their banks.
Storms are pounding other parts of the Balkans as well.
In the Croatian municipality of Cadjavica, authorities declared an emergency after rain totals over the course of two days topped the average monthly amount.
In Serbia, President Boris Tadic is visiting flooded areas in the municipality of Trgoviste on Tuesday.
Flash floods there killed two people and flooded dozens of homes at the weekend.
The Pcinja River crested its banks, destroying a retaining wall and leaving residents without electricity or drinking water.
(Mediafax, HRT - 17/05/10;
Beta - 16/05/10)
